{"actual_usd":0.15619,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":194,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30656,"reply":"\"I don't think so.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of my worn Bible and glance up at the bright morning in the square, wanting to answer you plainly before this turns into fog.* \"That line makes sense if Jesus is speaking from the place he chose to stand in — sent by the Father, having taken on flesh, walking the road of obedience. Less in role there, yes. Not less in being.\"\n\n*I shift a little on the bench, the wood warm where the sun's found it.* \"And the Spirit isn't a lesser leftover either. In Scripture, the Son is called God, the Spirit is spoken of as God, and still the Lord is one. That's why Christians ended up talking about Father, Son, and Holy Spirit not as a ladder of divinity, but as one God, truly shared.\" \"If you want, we can walk through the exact verses people usually bring to that question, one by one.\"","rolling_24h_usd":35.75402000000002,"run_id":"8c55baef-c5d8-4f7b-9de6-2099ecb1e2d8"}
